<title>SOUTH AFRICA: CRICKET-SOUTH AFRICA V INDIA SECOND TEST SCOREBOARD.</title>
<headline>CRICKET-SOUTH AFRICA V INDIA SECOND TEST SCOREBOARD.</headline>
<dateline>CAPE TOWN 1997-01-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Scoreboard on the fifth and final</p>
<p>day of the second test on Monday:</p>
<p>South Africa first innings 529-7 declared (G.Kirsten 103,</p>
<p>B.McMillan 103 not out, L.Klusener 102 not out, D.Cullinan 77)</p>
<p>India first innings 359 (S.Tendulkar 169, M.Azharuddin 115)</p>
<p>South Africa second innings 256-6 declared (A.Hudson 55,</p>
<p>D.Cullinan 55, B.McMillan 59 not out)</p>
<p>India second innings (overnight 52-3)</p>
<p> W.Raman c Richardson b Pollock	   16</p>
<p> N.Mongia b Donald			     2</p>
<p> R.Dravid cRichardson b Adams	     12</p>
<p> S.Ganguly c McMillan b Pollock	   30</p>
<p> S.Tendulkar c Klusener b McMillan	 9</p>
<p> M.Azharuddin c Hudson b Donald	    2</p>
<p> V.Laxman not out			     35</p>
<p> A.Kumble c Richardson b Adams	    14</p>
<p> D.Ganesh b Donald			     1</p>
<p> V.Prasad st Richardson b Adams	   15</p>
<p> J.Srinath absent injured		    0</p>
<p> Extras (lb-1, w-2, nb-5)		    8</p>
<p> Total					   144</p>
<p>Fall of wickets: 1-7 2-26 3-44 4-59 5-61 6-87 7-115 8-121</p>
<p>9-144</p>
<p>Bowling: Donald 18-5-40-3, Pollock 12-2-29-2, (4nb),</p>
<p>Klusener 9-3-13-0, McMillan 11-4-16-1, (1w), Adams 16.2-4-45-3</p>
<p>(1nb, 1w)</p>
<p>Result: South Africa won by 282 runs to take a winning 2-0</p>
<p>lead in the three-test series.</p>
<p>First test (Durban) - South Africa won by 328 runs.</p>
<p>Third Test: Johannesburg, January 16-20</p>
